- Political Constitutionalism (Bellamy, republican tradition): 3 papers - Democratic institutions themselves, not entrenched texts, provide legitimacy
- Deliberative Democracy (Habermas, Lafont, Chambers): 5 papers - Traditions of reasoned discourse essential for democratic legitimacy
